                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">The evidence of this witness, given on the former trial, was read over to him, to which he assented.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were these bills to which you refer Holcroft's trade bills? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> They were drawn by Holcroft on his customers, and amount to between 2,000<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. and 3,000<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—we had discounted trade bills of Holcroft's for four or five years—they came to me from Mr. Ramsay, who told me he received them from Durdin—when Ramsay called on me with reference to procuring a loan on the security of a bill of sale, he was alone—I never saw Durdin in company with him—Ramsay is the person with whom I negotiated, and I returned the money to him on the negotiation not being carried out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. GIFFARD</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Is Mr. Ramsay here to-day? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—this (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is the bill of sale.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
